0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & \log_2{20} & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & \log_2{30} \\
\end{matrix} \right]
\end{array}
</math>


First we can multiply <math>M</math> and <math>\mathrm{T}</math>. This will give us a matrix of [[generator-count vector]]s, or in other words, vectors representing versions of each of these target-intervals as they exist mapped by porcupine.


